              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Orchestration (Layer 2)</strong> — The LLM itself, typically operating inside an IDE like VS Code or Cursor. It reads the Directive, evaluates state, and selects which Execution script to run next. This layer handles the unforeseen: API failures, partial data, ambiguous outcomes.
              </li>
              <li>
                <strong class="text-white">Execution (Layer 3)</strong> — Modular, deterministic code (Python or TypeScript). A script like <code>send_email.py</code> doesn't reason—it accepts inputs and performs a single action with 100% reliability.
              </li>
            </ul>

            <p>
              By isolating reasoning from execution, the DOE Framework restores determinism where it matters while still leveraging intelligence where it creates leverage.
            </p>

